 Detectives in Despatch are investigating a case of culpable homicide following a fatal accident that happened over the weekend. According to police information, the accident happened at about 11:45Â on Saturday morning. "It is alleged that a 39-year-old male was traveling on the R75 (close to Despatch) with his motorbike in the direction of Port Elizabeth, when he allegedly lost control over the bike and was flung from it," described police spokesperson, Capt Gerda Swart. "He passed on at the scene. "The name of the deceased will be released after formal identification was done." 